Kismet

1. Overview
Kismet is an open-source wireless network detector, sniffer, and intrusion detection system that works with WiFi, Bluetooth, and SDR devices. It detects wireless networks, clients, and offers passive reconnaissance without associating with networks.

Use cases:
- Wireless network discovery  
- Passive sniffing / monitoring  
- Mapping WiFi & Bluetooth devices  
- Useful for wireless auditing and reconnaissance  

---

2. Key Features
- Passive detection of networks/devices  
- Supports many wireless cards & SDR  
- Logging to multiple formats (PCAP, Kismet logs)  
- Supports GPS tracking & mapping  
- Detection of hidden SSIDs  
- Alerts for suspicious activities  

---

3. Installation

Debian/Ubuntu/Kali
sudo apt update
sudo apt install kismet

Build from source (if needed)
git clone https://www.kismetwireless.net/git/kismet.git
cd kismet
./configure
make
sudo make install

----

4. Basic Usage
sudo kismet
